# Dockerfile Package Sorting

When adding packages to `apt-get install` commands in a `Dockerfile`, you MUST keep the package list sorted alphabetically. This improves readability and makes it easier to manage dependencies.

## Example

### Bad
```dockerfile
RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y \
    git \
    curl \
    build-essential
```

### Good
```dockerfile
RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y \
    build-essential \
    curl \
    git
```
